	9.

	                   STOCK OPTIONS and STOCK WARRANTS:




	 


	The Company has a stock option plan under which options to purchase shares of common stock may be granted to certain officers, directors and service providers.


	 


	In

	April 2014, the Company adopted a new Stock Option Plan (the “2014 Plan”). The 2014 Plan authorizes the issuance of up to 1,250,000 of the Company's common shares, subject to adjustment under certain circumstances. 


	The Company is listed on the TSX Venture Exchange ("

	TSX

	") and is subject to a limitation on the number of options a company may have. The 2014 Plan provides for the issuance of both incentive stock options and nonqualified options as those terms are defined in the

	Internal Revenue Code of 1986

	, as amended (the "

	Code

	").



	 


	During the years ended

	December 31, 2016 and 2015, the Company had no options granted, issued, exercised or outstanding.



	 


